<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-02-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-02-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="85" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d85">
                    <head>No. 391.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HF1" type="from">Fish</persName> to General <persName corresp="#p_DES1" type="to">Sickles</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-02-14"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 14,
                            1873</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>I understand from your telegrams of 12th and 13th that you have recognized
                        the new government. It will be grateful to know that you have regarded the
                        condition and prospects of the republic such as to justify the discretionary
                        power given you in that regard. This Government and people look with sincere
                        and earnest hope for the peaceful and permanent establishment of the new
                        government.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed><persName corresp="#p_HF1">FISH</persName>.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>